---

<section id="products" class="px-6 py-24 lg:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">The System</p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        One OS. Three ways in.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
        InferNode is the foundation. On top of it, choose the interface that
        fits how you work&mdash;from voice-first AI collaboration to a
        developer power tool.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Product cards -->
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">

      <!-- Stelle -->
      <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8 transition hover:border-node-cloud/50">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 h-32 w-32 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,_rgba(160,128,208,0.1)_0%,_transparent_70%)]"></div>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-node-cloud/10">
              <span class="text-lg text-node-cloud">&#9733;</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Stelle</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-node-cloud">Voice-first AI workspace</p>
          <p class="mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Stelle replaces the desktop with a conversational AI environment. Talk to your
            computer. The agent listens, acts, and presents results&mdash;documents,
            data, visualisations&mdash;without you ever opening an application.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-cloud">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">Voice-controlled</strong> &mdash; speak naturally, the agent acts</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-cloud">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">Three-zone interface</strong> &mdash; conversation, presentation, and context at a glance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-cloud">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">No apps to learn</strong> &mdash; the agent composes capabilities from your namespace</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Veltro -->
      <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8 transition hover:border-accent/50">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 h-32 w-32 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,_rgba(224,96,48,0.1)_0%,_transparent_70%)]"></div>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-accent/10">
              <span class="text-lg text-accent">&#9654;</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Veltro</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-accent">The unchained agent</p>
          <p class="mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Veltro is an AI agent that lives in your namespace, not inside an application.
            It reads files, invokes tools, queries LLMs, and spawns sub-agents&mdash;all
            within the boundaries you define.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">Namespace-isolated</strong> &mdash; can only see what you grant</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">Sub-agents</strong> &mdash; spawn child agents with even fewer capabilities</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-accent">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">LLM as a filesystem</strong> &mdash; mount any model at <code class="font-mono text-xs text-accent">/n/llm</code></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Xenith -->
      <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8 transition hover:border-node-jetson/50">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 h-32 w-32 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top_right,_rgba(80,200,120,0.1)_0%,_transparent_70%)]"></div>
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-node-jetson/10">
              <span class="text-lg text-node-jetson">&#9638;</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Xenith</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-node-jetson">Developer power tool</p>
          <p class="mb-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            A text environment built for developers and AI agents working side by side.
            Forked from Acme with async I/O, dark mode, and a 9P interface that lets
            agents interact through file operations&mdash;no SDK required.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-jetson">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">9P filesystem interface</strong> &mdash; agents read and write, no API needed</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-jetson">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">Observable</strong> &mdash; all agent activity visible to humans in real time</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="mt-0.5 text-node-jetson">&#8227;</span>
              <span class="text-text-muted"><strong class="text-text">GPU-accelerated</strong> &mdash; SDL3 with Metal, Vulkan, and D3D backends</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Foundation bar -->
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-6 text-center">
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-2 sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm text-accent">;</span>
        <span class="text-sm text-text-muted">
          <strong class="text-text">InferNode</strong> &mdash; the 64-bit Inferno&reg; OS that runs beneath it all.
          15 MB RAM. 2-second startup. 630+ utilities. Bell Labs lineage.
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
